<div id="banner">
	<h1>JavaScript Form Validation Done Right</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>A long time ago, I believe on Netscape&#8217;s site, I saw JavaScript form validation done Right. Next to each required field was a red circe with an X in white. As you correctly entered a response in the field, the icon changed to a green circle with a white check. It was such a great design I still remember it to this day. Unfortunately, I can&#8217;t find it. Does anyone know where this is&#8230; or at least know where to get these icons? I suspect I&#8217;ll just have to rewrite it myself.</p>

<p>*Update 2003-09-07:* I went ahead and rewrote it. If anyone else is interested, I put together <a href="http://notabug.com/qweb/bbbbb">a modern equivalent</a>.</p>

<p class="posted">posted September 03, 2002 12:07 PM (<a class="category" href="cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000559" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
